<DOC><DOCNO> AP891222-0124 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-22-89 1346EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Israel     12-22 0452</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Israel,0467</SECOND><HEAD>Soldiers Kill 3 Palestinians in West Bank</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Israeli soldiers shot and killed threePalestinians in the occupied West Bank on Friday, including the16-year-old sister of a suspect they sought to apprehend in avillage raid, Arab reports said.   The army confirmed two deaths from the village raid and said thesuspect was among the seven people wounded in Jaba village. He wasidentified by Arab reporters as Mohammed Taysir Alawneh, 22, whohad been sought for anti-Israeli activities in the two-yearPalestinian uprising.   The deaths came a day after Israeli troops shot and killed twoPalestinians in a similar raid in the nearby village of Beit Furik.   In a separate incident, soldiers fatally wounded 19-year-oldYaacoub Ramahi in a clash with stonethrowing youths in the town ofEl-Bireh, Arab reporters said.   Israel radio said the youth was part of a group of maskedPalestinians throwing building blocks and iron bars at a militarypatrol.   An army spokesman said the military was investigating theincident.   Also Friday, a 12-year-old Palestinian boy from Bethlehem diedof wounds reportedly suffered when an Israeli civilian fired on himfour months ago.   The child, who died at Jerusalem's Mukassed Hospital, wasMohammed Jamil Eid Kamel. He had been paralyzed since Aug. 7, whenPalestinian witnesses reported he was shot in the neck by a passingIsraeli motorist.   A general strike to mourn Kamel's death closed shops andbusinesses Friday in Bethlehem, residents said. Hundreds ofChristian pilgrims are expected in the biblical town startingSunday for the Christmas holiday.   The latest deaths raised to 637 the number of Arabs killed byIsraelis since the Palestinian revolt against Israeli rule began inthe occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip in December 1987.   At least 161 other Palestinians have been slain by fellow Arabs,most on suspicion of collaboration with Israel. Forty-threeIsraelis also have died in the violence.   The army said soldiers ``met resistance'' during a Friday raidin Jaba, six miles north of Nablus.   As troops were trying to enter the home of a suspect, an officerfired in self-defense when he was attacked by a Palestinian womanwith a knife, the army said. The woman was killed, and the officerslightly wounded, it said.   Arab reports said she was Asmahan Taysir Alawneh, 16, the sisterof the suspect.   The army quoted hospital officials as saying a Palestinianteen-ager was fatally shot in a subsequent stone-throwing clashwith troops in Jaba. Arab reports identified him as Iyad MohammedSaid Hassan, 18.   Nine Palestinians were shot and wounded in stone-throwingclashes with Israeli troops in the Gaza Strip on Friday, Arabreports said. The army said it was checking the reports.</TEXT></DOC>